{
  "id": "8c5fb6eb73604b2aa709a0b4a310ffd9",
  "title": "Blackmagic Design Media Player",
  "description": "Implements a media player for Blackmagic Design DeckLink card.",
  "longDescription": "<h2><strong>Blackmagic Design</strong></h2><p><br /></p><p>The Blackmagic Media Plugin enables users to natively send SDI video in and out of the Unreal Engine. Whether it is Virtual Production, Film, or Broadcast Television, SDI video allows for frame accurate, low latency, high quality video. Support for Timecode, Genlock, allow for the Unreal Engine to be used seamlessly with professional video pipelines.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Technical Details</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><a href=\"https://docs.unrealengine.com/en-us/Engine/ProVideoIO\" rel=\"nofollow\">Professional Video I/O</a></p><p><a href=\"https://docs.unrealengine.com/en-US/Engine/ProVideoIO/TimecodeGenlock\" rel=\"nofollow\">Timecode and Genlock</a></p><p><br /></p><p>Support for DeckLink line cards</p><br /><b>UE-Only Content</b> - Licensed for Use Only with Unreal Engine-based Products",
  "technicalDetails": "<p>Features:</p><ul><li>Capture a SDI input feed with Blackmagic Media Player.</li><li>HD video are supported with progressive and interlaced standard.</li><li>Read audio and timecode.</li><li>Can synchronize the input with the engine&#39;s timecode.</li><li>Grab a UE4 rendered image and output it with SDI feed with Blackmagic Output.</li><li>Genlock the engine with Blackmagic Custom Time Step.</li><li>Control the engine&#39;s timecode with Blackmagic Timecode Provider.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Code Modules:</p><ul><li>BlackmagicMedia</li><li>BlackmagicMediaOutput</li><li>BlackmagicMediaFactory</li><li>BlackmagicMediaEditor</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Supported Development Platforms: Win64</p><p>Supported Target Build Platforms: Win64</p><p>Documentation: https://docs.unrealengine.com/en-us/Engine/ProVideoIO</p><p>Example Project: From the learn tab, the sample &#34;Virtual Studio&#34; is an example of how you can use Blackmagic DeckLink in your project. https://unrealengine.com/learn/virtual-studio</p><p>Important/Additional Notes: The plugin has been tested with the DeckLink 8K Pro, DeckLink Duo 2 and the DeckLink 4K Extreme 12G.</p>",
